Description: Replace MIDAS Sound System with libopenmpt + SDL2 audio
 MIDAS is unmaintained, 32-bit only and not available in current Debian/Ubuntu
 archives as an i386 package.  Replaces all MIDAS calls with:
  - SDL2 audio device (SDL_OpenAudioDevice) driving a streaming callback.
  - libopenmpt for module decoding (XM, IT, MOD, S3M, …).  libopenmpt
    exposes current order/row, preserving the TBL3 demo-sync mechanism that
    MIDAS provided via MIDASgetPlayStatus().
  - Music is now loaded directly from the in-memory decompressed buffer via
    openmpt_module_create_from_memory2(), eliminating the temporary-file
    round-trip that existed in both PlayMusic() and fardoint()/TBL1.
  - Thread safety: audio callback and main thread share openmpt_mod under
    an SDL_mutex.
  - Build dependency updated: libmidas-dev removed, libopenmpt-dev added.
Generated-by: Claude Sonnet 4.6
Reviewed-by: Nicolas HOUDELOT <nicolas@demosdebs.org>
